      {
        "id": 2491745,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-09-28T10:26:58.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"146064\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"146064\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Killer pairing, Carlos!</p>\n<p>Beaucastel speaks to me with its mourvedre cut, love the meaty quality.</p>\n<p>Just curious, what were the stated ABVs?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Rayas 14%<br>\nBeaucastel 13.5%</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>When you drink a bottle of the 1989 Rayas, it feels considerably more than that. I would guess &gt; 15%.</p>",
